narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned how to be accountable for my own time and work independently.
I gained skills in forming original research hypotheses, computational neuroimaging methods, and troubleshooting roadblocks in the research process.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Weakness: Not quite sure what the head professors wanted out of us for final papers and presentations. Expectations were unclear or ambiguous.
As this is an independent project rather than a formal course, there were no systematic strengths and weaknesses.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you are a neuroscience major, you should do an empirical research project for your senior requirement! Its challenging but youll learn a lot and accomplish something cool.
